Awesome! Let’s dive into Java Networking, focusing on:

🔌 Sockets (TCP/IP communication)

🌐 HTTP communication using HttpURLConnection and modern HttpClient

This is useful not just for backend work — but also for automation testers who:

Simulate client-server interactions

Validate API connectivity

Send mock HTTP requests

Test socket-based systems (rare but real)


1. Java Sockets (TCP Client-Server Model)
🔧 How It Works:
Component	Role
ServerSocket	Listens for incoming client connections
Socket	Represents the connection between client and server